  "@type": "Article",
  "description": "I changed the name of \u0026ldquo;Curio Shop\u0026rdquo; to \u0026ldquo;Barnabus\u0026rdquo; before the first commit. Both names are inspired by Teraum, specifically a store formerly run by Barnabus Trent, which sold items from around the world to people in Bellybrush and Ack. The notion being, those items were stripped of context, reduced to little bits of curiosity. That\u0026rsquo;s true of the data being presented here as clobbered-together HTML. But! Made the first commit: I have something that can read some Lua data and make an HTML file. Wonderful.\n",
